SIMPLE: minority
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minority
<hw>Mi*nor"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Minorities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>minorit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Minor</er>, <pos>a. &
n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being a minor, or under age.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>State of being less or small.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The smaller number; -- opposed to
<ant>majority</ant>; <as>as, the <ex>minority</ex> must be ruled by the
majority</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Those members of a legislature that belong to the
political party which is in the minority in that institution; <as>as,
the bill will pass even if the <ex>minority</ex> are strongly
opposed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>minor league</ent>⟦br⟧
